header: MacWithIvTest is intended for testing MACs that use an IV for randomization.

ModifiedTag.description: The test vector contains a modified MAC. The purpose of the test is to check whether the verification fully checks the tag.

Pseudorandom.description: The test vector contains pseudorandomly generated inputs. The goal of the test vector is to check the correctness of the implementation for various sizes of the input parameters. Some libraries do not support all the parameter sizes. In particular the size of the IV is often restricted.

SpecialCaseTag.description: The test vector has been constructed such that the tag is a special case. Such a construction is done by fixing the tag and then computing a message from the tag.
